snippet: Some advocates praised a group of Mexican immigrants who tried to enter the country in a protest, but others said their tactics distracted from the fight in Washington.
abstract: Protest by nine Mexican immigrants in which they tried to enter country through border station in Arizona even though they had no valid documents has provoked an unusual public argument among groups pushing Congress to overhaul the immigration laws.

byline.original: By JULIA PRESTON and REBEKAH ZEMANSKY
byline.contributor: Julia Preston reported from New York, and Rebekah Zemansky from Phoenix.

lead_paragraph: Some advocates praised a group of Mexican immigrants who tried to enter the country in a protest, but others said their tactics distracted from the fight in Washington.

headline.main: Demonstration at Arizona Border Divides Supporters of Immigration Overhaul
